      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/4/21/8",
      "text": [
        " \"نَعَمْ وَ إِنْ مَاتَ وَرِثَتْهُ وَ إِنْ مَاتَتْ لَمْ يَرِثْهَا\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4882 - In a narration from Hammad through Al-Halabi, it is reported that Abu Abdullah (as) was asked about a man who was on his deathbed and divorced his wife. He was asked whether such a divorce was permissible.\nImam (as) replied: \"Yes, it is permissible. If he dies, she will inherit from him, but if she dies, he will not inherit from her.\""
        ]
      }
    },
